            One complication that arises from this character is that a majority
            of his damage relies on the rogues sneak attack(hyperlink) ability
            as that adds 3d6 dice worth of damage on a single attack per turn.
            However this ability is only available under special conditions,
            mainly being having no disadvantage on an attack (2d20 take lower)
            and having advantage on it (2d20 take higher)
          </p>

          <p class="panel">
            Here I'll include 3 graphs, one for average damage without sneak
            attack, average damage with sneak attack, and a final one for max
            possible damage (crit potential)
          </p>

